{
  "texts": [
    "Whether the information provided is correct or not is immaterial: when LLMs produce outputs that contain the names and bibliographical information of real people, they are processing personal data.",
    "Additionally, individuals can often be easily identified from the context of the text prompt or text output, or by using search engines.",
    "LLMs linked to search engines may also facilitate identification.",
    "Particularly in the case of public LLMs, it is likely that many data subjects can be identified for the reasons mentioned above (Pesch & B ö hme, 2023).",
    "It is important to note that the people in the training data are not theoretically the same as those produced in the output data even where they have the same name, as LLMs can also generate names of existing people, for example, by producing information which can then be assigned by users."
  ]
}